      "content": "A high-pitched squealing sound after a brake job on a Camry is often a sign of something catching, and you should check the brake pads and rotors first. Look closely at the pads to see if they are seated correctly or if any debris is trapped between them. If you see anything, you might need to clean that area, or perhaps a little bit of grease will help things settle down, though don't overdo it.",
