    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "yeah i thought it might be debris but i cleaned it out with some brake cleaner and it didn't help at all. the sound is really weird though, it's almost like it's intermittent and comes and goes. could there be something else hidden in there making that noise that i can't see easily?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If cleaning the obvious debris didn't work, then you're dealing with something more subtle, like a loose bolt or a failing component. Intermittent noises are often the trickiest, suggesting something is only catching under specific conditions, like when the caliper moves or the rotor spins. You might need to check the caliper slide pins—those little pins that allow the caliper to move freely. If they are binding, it can cause that intermittent squeal.",
      "source": "target",
